Here’s the PlantUML spec for **LCP-UML-1** with 30+ distinct classes, explicit inheritance, and key compositions across TrafficFlow, PublicTransit, and EmergencyResponse.

```plantuml
@startuml LCP-UML-1
title Smart City Traffic & Infrastructure Grid

'---------------- Traffic Flow ----------------
package "TrafficFlow" {
  class CityControlCenter
  class TrafficFlowManager
  class TrafficSensor
  class SignalController
  class Intersection
  class RoadSegment
  class DynamicMessageSign
  class PedestrianCrossing
  class BicycleLane
  class CCTVCamera
  class WeatherStation
  class AirQualitySensor
  class DataAnalyticsPlatform
}

CityControlCenter *-- TrafficFlowManager
CityControlCenter *-- EmergencyResponseCenter
CityControlCenter *-- DataAnalyticsPlatform
TrafficFlowManager *-- Intersection
TrafficFlowManager *-- DynamicMessageSign
TrafficFlowManager o-- RoadSegment
Intersection *-- SignalController
Intersection *-- TrafficSensor
Intersection *-- PedestrianCrossing
Intersection *-- CCTVCamera
RoadSegment o-- BicycleLane
TrafficSensor ..> DataAnalyticsPlatform : sends data
WeatherStation ..> DataAnalyticsPlatform
AirQualitySensor ..> DataAnalyticsPlatform
SignalController ..> TrafficFlowManager : status
DynamicMessageSign ..> TrafficFlowManager : updates

'---------------- Public Transit ----------------
package "PublicTransit" {
  class PublicTransitHub
  class TransitRoute
  class TicketingSystem
  class FareValidator
  class Passenger
  class Vehicle
  class ElectricBus
  class LightRail
  class AutonomousShuttle
  class ChargingStation
  class MaintenanceSchedule
  class MaintenanceCrew
}

PublicTransitHub *-- TransitRoute
PublicTransitHub *-- TicketingSystem
TicketingSystem *-- FareValidator
TransitRoute o-- Vehicle
Vehicle <|-- ElectricBus
Vehicle <|-- LightRail
Vehicle <|-- AutonomousShuttle
ElectricBus *-- ChargingStation
ChargingStation *-- GridPowerMonitor
GridPowerMonitor *-- EnergyStorageUnit
GridPowerMonitor o-- SolarArray
MaintenanceSchedule *-- MaintenanceCrew
Vehicle ..> MaintenanceSchedule
Passenger --> TransitRoute : rides
FareValidator --> Passenger : validates
AutonomousShuttle ..> TrafficSensor : V2I feed

'---------------- Emergency Response ----------------
package "EmergencyResponse" {
  class EmergencyResponseCenter
  class IncidentReport
  class PriorityCorridor
  class EmergencyVehicle
  class Ambulance
  class FireTruck
  class PoliceCar
}

EmergencyResponseCenter *-- IncidentReport
EmergencyResponseCenter *-- PriorityCorridor
EmergencyResponseCenter o-- EmergencyVehicle
EmergencyVehicle <|-- Ambulance
EmergencyVehicle <|-- FireTruck
EmergencyVehicle <|-- PoliceCar
PriorityCorridor ..> SignalController : preemption
IncidentReport ..> DataAnalyticsPlatform : analytics
EmergencyVehicle ..> TrafficFlowManager : ETA/route

'---------------- Energy & Infra ----------------
class GridPowerMonitor
class EnergyStorageUnit
class SolarArray

'---------------- Additional relations ----------------
DataAnalyticsPlatform ..> TrafficFlowManager : optimization insights
DataAnalyticsPlatform ..> PublicTransitHub : demand forecasts
MaintenanceCrew ..> EmergencyResponseCenter : incident cleanup
LightRail ..> GridPowerMonitor : power draw
@enduml
```

- Inheritance shown via `<|--` (Vehicle → ElectricBus/LightRail/AutonomousShuttle; EmergencyVehicle → Ambulance/FireTruck/PoliceCar).
- Compositions shown via `*--` (e.g., Intersection contains SignalController, TrafficSensor; PublicTransitHub contains TransitRoute and TicketingSystem; EmergencyResponseCenter contains IncidentReport, PriorityCorridor).
- Project name encoded as diagram title and filename label `LCP-UML-1`.

