The update introduces a database schema file and configures controllers to use a serializable isolation level for POST, PUT, and DELETE operations to ensure data consistency. It also implements ghost write concurrency control using a rowversion column. Key files include the schema definition and controller files managing these transactions. There are currently no automated tests in the codebase. Note that the NuGet restore failed due to the environment being offline, so running `dotnet restore` will be necessary once network access is available.
